           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01">
 	<p n="1-3">Sruk Viṣṇupura <supplied reason="explanation">A</supplied>: Si Pandan, 11 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 4 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 15 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, 3 boys at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, a girl at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied>, 2 baby boys <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, 3 baby girls <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>; total 20.</p>
              <p n="3-5">Sruk <gap reason="lost"/>, 2 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>, 3 boys at the age or running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>; total 20. Among the <foreign>lvan</foreign>, there are a male slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied> and 2 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>; total 3.</p>
              <p n="5-8">Sruk Viṣṇupura <supplied reason="explanation">B</supplied>: Si <gap reason="lost"/>, Si Candrodaya, 16 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 2 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 14 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, a male slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>, 5 boys at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, 2 girls at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied>, a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>, 2 <foreign>tai a</foreign>; total 44. Among the <foreign>lvan</foreign>, there are a male slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied> and a female slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>; total 2.</p>
              <p n="8-12">Sruk Stuk Phlyāṅ: Si Mr̥dulakṣmi, Si Dharmmeśvara, 11 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 9 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 10 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, 5 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>, 3 boys at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, 3 girls at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied>, 3 baby girls <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>, 2 <foreign>tai a</foreign>; total 48. Among the <foreign>lvan</foreign>, there are a male slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 2 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, a female slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>; total 4.</p>
              <p n="12-23">Sruk Vrai Diṅ: Si Kan-as, Gho Toyada, Gho Amara, Gho Kanloñ, Gho Panlas, Gho Padmaruci, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Thgap, Gho Vāmaśiva, Gho Dhi<gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Jīva, Gho Vrahmaruci, Gho Kavirāja, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Saṁ-ap, <gap reason="lost"/> Candrabhāra, Gho Kan-as, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kaṁ Vraḥ, acommpanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Panso, tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kaṁpit, another Tai Kaṁpit, <gap reason="lost"/>, another Tai Kaṁ Vraḥ accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied> and <gap reason="lost"/> girl(s) at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied>, <gap reason="lost"/>; total 36. Among the <foreign>lvan</foreign>, there are Gho Dharmmasoma <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kaṁpit accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>; total 4.</p>
              <p n="23-30">Sruk <gap reason="lost"/>: Si Hr̥dayaśiva, Gho Pandan, Gho Kaṁpit, <gap reason="lost"/> Khñuṁ, Gho Kaṁvrau, another Gho Kaṁpit, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl Saṁ-ap, Gvāl Aṅkāṁ, Gval Kañcān, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Khnāṅ, Tai Jvik, Tai Thleṅ, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Phnos, Tai Kantr̥p, Tai Snaṁ, Tai Saṁ-ap, <gap reason="lost"/>, a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>, 5 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 4 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 9 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>; total 20.</p>
              <p n="30-33">Sruk Mahāloha: Si Vrahma, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kansip, Gho Krau, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kan-in, Tai Kanso, <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai A Kan-in, Tai A Phtal, Tai A Saṁ-ap</p><!-- kuch: The text may be continued in K.183-9. -->
                   </div> 
